This paper deals with optimization of risk-sensitive criteria in sequential decision-making problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on actor-critic algorithms, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with control applications, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
